headline: GameStop earnings, JOLTS labor data: What to Watch
summary: Asking for a Trend host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Tuesday, Dec. 9. AutoZone (AZO) and Campbell's (CPB) report earnings in the morning, while Casey's General Stores (CASY), AeroVironment (AVAV), GameStop (GME), and Cracker Barrel (CBRL) report in the afternoon. The Small Business Administration's (SBA's) National Federation of Independent Business (NFIB) Small Business Optimism Index for the month of November will be published in the morning. Economists expect a reading of 98.3, a slight uptick from the previous month's 98.2. The US Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) will release the delayed results for October's Job Openings and Labor Turnover Survey (JOLTS) in the morning. Economists expect the number to hold steady from the previous month at 7.2 million. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Asking for a Trend.
